These are the shortcuts for TMUX I found after hours of search:

1) New Window
    ctrl + a <release> c;

2) New Horizontal window in same screen
    ctrl + a <release> Shift + %

3) New Vertical window
    ctrl + a <release> Shift + "

2-A, 3-A) Move between panes
            ctrl + a <release> arrow ( any one of these ----> Up, Down, Left, Right)

4) View and move between Sessions
    ctrl + a <release> w

5) Rename Windows
    ctrl + a <release> ,

6) Named Sessions
    tmux new -s <name of session>

7) Kill all servers
    tmux kill-servers

8) Dettach from a session but keep it running in background
    ctrl + a <release> d

9) Re-attach to a session which is already running in background
    tmux attach-session -t <name of session>

10) Scrolling and copy and paste
    to copy paste we have to be in scrolling mode
        Scroll Mode:
            ctrl + a <release the key> [
            ESC key to get out of this mode
        copy:
            ctrl + space-bar to select or highlight <move cursor after releasing this keycombination>
            Alt + w to copy it to clipboard
        paste:
            in TMUX:
                ctrl + a <release the key> ]
            in other programs or apps:
                ctrl + v <to anywhere you want to paste, try it on notepad.exe>
        Search in Scroll Mode:
            ctrl + r <at the bottom type the text you are looking for>
                use n key for next in search or shift+n
